        "scenario": "Transient database connection error (network blip, TCP reset)",
        "handling": "unhandled",
        "recommendation": "CRITICAL: No retry on connection errors means a single dropped packet returns 500 to the user. Implement retry with exponential backoff (1-2 retries, short timeout). Most connection errors are transient and resolve in <1 second."
