    "retry_config": "NONE. Zero retries on any database operation. This is the single easiest improvement with the highest impact — even 1 retry with 500ms backoff would eliminate most transient 500s.",
    "timeout_config": "NOT SPECIFIED. No mention of connection timeout, query timeout, or pool acquisition timeout. All three must be explicitly configured: connection_timeout=3s, query_timeout=5s, pool_timeout=2s as starting points.",
    "circuit_breakers": "NONE. If the primary goes down, every request will attempt a connection, fail, and return 500. A circuit breaker would fail-fast after N consecutive errors, reducing load on the recovering database and giving faster error responses.",
    "graceful_degradation": "NONE. No fallback behavior — every database error is a 500. For a read-heavy service, consider: serving stale cached results, returning partial data, or returning a clear 'temporarily unavailable' with Retry-After header instead of generic 500."
  },

